  "text": "The results presented here describe the mchB gene, which had previously been identified as one of the four mch genes required for the synthesis of MccH47 [CITATION_1] . This small ORF is now proposed to be the structural gene for the antibiotic, and this would therefore lead us to conclude that MccH47 is indeed a ribosomally synthesized peptide antibiotic.",
